Package ss.project.strategy

Interface Strategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NaiveStrategy, SmartStrategy
    public interface Strategy
    A strategy interface for reusability and for defining the core methods for a strategy. A model class as it implements the AI strategy.
    Author:
    Alex Petrov (s2478412) and Kagan Gulsum (s2596091)

        int[] determineMove​(Board board)
        The method for determining the move of the AI.
        Parameters:
        board - The board onto which the move will be determined.
        Returns:
        An integer array where the first value is the first move to make, and the second value (if not -1) is the second move to make.
        Requires
        board != null
        Ensures
        \result[0] >= 0 && 27 >= \result[0] && \result[1] >= -1 && 27 >= \result[1]
